<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <%- include('partials/head', { title }) %>
  <body>
    <%- include('partials/site-header') %>

    <main class="page">
      <div class="layout-narrow">
        <article>
          <header class="page-intro">
            <h1>About me</h1>
          </header>

          <figure class="article-hero">
            <img src="/assets/author.svg" alt="Portrait of Anna Weber" width="1200" height="600" />
            <figcaption>Anna Weber</figcaption>
          </figure>

          <div class="article-body">
            <p>
              Hi, I&rsquo;m <strong>Anna Weber</strong> — a software developer based in
              Berlin who spends far too much of her free time in the mountains.
            </p>
            <p>
              I started this blog to keep a record of the trips I take, the things I
              cook, and the small experiments I run with web technology. It now runs on
              Node.js with server-side rendering and a SQLite database.
            </p>
            <h2>What you&rsquo;ll find here</h2>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Travel</strong> — slow, car-free journeys across Europe.</li>
              <li><strong>Tech</strong> — notes on building simple, durable software.</li>
              <li><strong>Food</strong> — the recipes I actually cook on weeknights.</li>
              <li><strong>Life</strong> — everything that doesn&rsquo;t fit the boxes above.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              Want to say hello or suggest a topic? The
              <a href="/contact">contact page</a> is the best way to reach me.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </main>

    <%- include('partials/footer') %>
  </body>
</html>
